[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Laura Buhl Evelyn Weiss digital product tools workflow View Using Tool | Search AI tool to generate printable planner layouts SVG PDF View Using Tool | Search how to use Midjourney for planner pages View Using Tool | Search Poddin.io features for printables View Using Tool | Search Planify Pro AI features View continue This is a straight-shooting, tactical playbook for building a high-end planner business without touching Adobe or Canva. You mentioned Laura Buhl and Evelyn Weiss. These creators succeed because they treat planners as systems, not just \"pretty pages.\" To match their quality without their complex tech stack (InDesign), you cannot rely on generic \"prompt-to-image\" AI (like DALL-E) for the grids because AI is terrible at keeping straight lines and accurate dates. Instead, we will use a Hybrid AI Stack: The Brain (Copy/Strategy): ChatGPT / Claude (for the planner \"system\"). The Engine (Layout Automation): Planify Pro. This is the specialized SaaS you are looking for. It is not \"generative\" (guessing lines); it is \"parametric\" (automating perfect grids). It is the closest thing to \"InDesign in a browser\" for planners. The Beauty (Assets): Midjourney or Kittl. The \"No-Code\" Planner Tech Stack Tool\tRole\tWhy this matches your profile Planify Pro\tLayout Generator\tIt is dedicated solely to planners. You don't drag lines; you select \"Weekly Vertical\" and it generates the grid instantly. It handles dates automatically (no typing \"Jan 1, Jan 2...\"). Kittl\tVector Design\tThe \"Anti-Canva.\" It uses AI to generate vector graphics (SVG) which print perfectly sharp at any size. Essential for high-end feel. Claude 3.5 Sonnet\tProduct Architect\tWrites the \"prompts\" and the thoughtful reflection questions that make the planner valuable. Tactical SOP: The \"AI Planner Architect\" Workflow Objective: Create a high-ticket \"CEO Productivity Planner\" printable PDF ready for Etsy/Shopify. Phase 1: The \"Offer\" Architecture (Input) Tool: Claude 3.5 Sonnet or ChatGPT Step\tAction\tExpected Input (Prompt)\tExpected Output & Rationale 1.1\tDefine the System\t\"Act as a productivity expert like James Clear. Create a unique daily planner framework for [Target Audience: e.g., ADHD Entrepreneurs]. It needs 3 distinct sections: Morning Mindset, Deep Work Blocks, and Evening Audit. Give me the specific labels for the grid headers.\"\tOutput: A structural outline (e.g., \"The Dopamine Menu,\" \"Focus 3x3\"). Rationale: You are selling a result, not paper. Unique headers distinguish you from generic templates. 1.2\tGenerate Copy\t\"Write 50 unique 'daily reflection' questions based on Stoic philosophy, short enough to fit in a planner footer.\"\tOutput: A CSV or list of quotes/questions. Rationale: High-value planners guide the user; they don't just provide empty space. Phase 2: The Layout Automation (The \"Heavy Lifting\") Tool: Planify Pro (Web-based SaaS) Step\tAction\tDetailed Walkthrough\tExpected Output 2.1\tGlobal Setup\t1. Login to Planify Pro. 2. Set Page Size to A5 or US Letter (Standard for home printing). 3. Set Margins to 15mm (Safe for hole punching).\tA blank canvas with print-safe boundaries pre-set. 2.2\tThe Grid Gen\t1. Click \"Layout Generator\" on the left menu. 2. Select \"Weekly\" or \"Daily\" module. 3. Key Move: Do not draw boxes. Drag the \"Schedule\" widget onto the page. It automatically creates time slots (e.g., 6 AM - 9 PM).\tA mathematically perfect grid. No manual spacing or \"eyeballing\" required. 2.3\tData Automation\t1. In the sidebar, look for \"Date Range.\" 2. Select \"Undated\" (for evergreen printables) or \"2026\" (for dated). 3. Toggle \"Holidays\" if you want them auto-filled.\tA fully dated or undated grid structure without typing a single number. 2.4\tCustom Injection\t1. Take the \"Header Labels\" from Phase 1 (e.g., change \"Notes\" to \"Brain Dump\"). 2. Click the text field in the widget and paste your custom label.\tA layout that looks custom-coded but was built using widgets. 2.5\tExport\t1. Click Export. 2. Select PDF (High Quality / 300 DPI). 3. Crucial: Select \"CMYK\" if available for professional printing, or \"RGB\" for home printing.\tA crisp, professional PDF file. Phase 3: Aesthetic Injection (The \"Vibe\") Tool: Kittl (Web-based AI Design Tool) Note: We use Kittl because it exports SVGs. Midjourney makes JPEGs (raster), which can look pixelated if printed large. Kittl is safer for text/vectors. Step\tAction\tDetailed Walkthrough\tExpected Output 3.1\tCover Design\t1. Open Kittl. 2. Use the \"AI Text-to-Vector\" tool. 3. Prompt: \"Minimalist botanical line art, organic shapes, boho style, black and white, vector.\"\tA scalable vector graphic for your cover that won't blur. 3.2\tTypography\t1. Use Kittl’s text warping tools to create a logo for your planner (e.g., \"The 2026 Founder's Journal\"). 2. Export as Transparent PNG (300 DPI).\tA high-end branding asset to overlay on your Planify Pro file. 3.3\tFinal Assembly\tOption A: Import the Kittl images into Planify Pro as stickers/images. Option B: Use a PDF Merger (like I Love PDF) to combine the Kittl Cover + Planify Interior.\tThe final \"Product\" ready for sale. Monetization & Sales Strategy As a SaaS founder and Marketer, here is how you leverage this asset. 1. The \"Iterative\" Product Ladder Don't just sell one PDF. Create a \"Stack.\" Tier 1 (Lead Magnet): \"The One-Page Daily Audit\" (Free). Tier 2 (Tripwire - $9): \"The 30-Day Project Sprint Planner\" (Printable). Tier 3 (Core Offer - $27): \"The Full Year CEO System\" (Dated + Undated versions). 2. The \"Hybrid\" Implementation Since you are a \"digital offer course creator,\" bundling the Printable Planner with a Mini-Course (video walkthrough of how to use the planner) increases the perceived value from $10 (commodity) to $47 (solution). 3. Interactive Marketing Assets (Infographic Strategy) Use Napkin.ai (a new tool for docs) or Kittl to create flowcharts showing why your planner layout works. Visual: \"The Old Way (Messy List)\" vs \"The New Way (Time-Blocked Grid).\" Process: Show the \"Before and After\" of a messy desk vs. your planner page. Knowledge Base Management To organize this in your Gmail/Drive: Create a folder [PRODUCT] Planner 2026. Subfolders: 01_Strategy_Prompts, 02_Raw_Assets_Kittl, 03_Working_Files_Planify, 04_Final_PDFs. Store the CSV of the 50 reflection questions (from Phase 1) in 01_Strategy_Prompts so you can reuse them for social media content later. Why this avoids the \"Canva Trap\" Canva is great, but for planners, it is manual. If you want to change the date on 365 pages in Canva, you have to type it 365 times or use a complex \"Bulk Create\" CSV method that often breaks formatting. Planify Pro handles the \"logic\" of the calendar (dates, leap years, holidays) automatically, saving you dozens of hours of grunt work. any alternative to planner pro This is a common friction point. Planify Pro is excellent, but it can be pricey or have a learning curve some users dislike. If we are moving away from Canva/Adobe (manual design) and Planify Pro (dedicated SaaS), we need to look at automation tools that use data to build pages. Here are the top 3 tactical alternatives for a \"non-coder\" that still automate the heavy lifting of dates and grids. The Top Alternatives Analysis Tool\tBest For\tTechnical Level\tWhy It Works for You Poddin.io (or similar \"Low-Code\" generators)\tMinimalist/Clean Grids\tLow\tVery fast generation of standard grids. Good for \"base\" layers. Piktochart AI\tVisual/Infographic Style\tLow-Mid\tStronger on the \"design\" side than standard planner tools. Google Sheets + Autocrat (The \"Hacker\" Method)\tComplete Customization\tMid (No Code, just Logic)\tMy Top Recommendation. You own the data. It's free. It scales infinitely. Recommendation: The \"Google Sheets + Autocrat\" Method As a SaaS founder and digital marketer, you will appreciate this method most. It separates your \"Data\" (Dates, Quotes, Holidays) from your \"Design\" (Google Slides layout). It allows you to generate 365 unique pages in 3 minutes for free. Why this wins: Zero Subscription Cost: It uses free Google Workspace tools. Scalability: Want to translate the planner into Spanish? Just translate the spreadsheet column. Done. Accuracy: Excel logic handles the dates; no manual typing errors. Tactical SOP: The \"Sheet-to-Slide\" Generator Workflow Objective: Create a 365-day dated planner with unique daily quotes without drawing a single box manually. Phase 1: The Database (The Brain) Tool: Google Sheets Step\tAction\tExpected Input\tExpected Output & Rationale 1.1\tCreate Data Sheet\tOpen a new Google Sheet. Create headers in Row 1: Date, DayOfWeek, Month, DailyQuote, FocusArea.\tOutput: A structured database. Rationale: This file acts as the \"API\" for your planner. 1.2\tAutomate Dates\t1. In cell A2, type 1/1/2026. 2. In cell A3, type =A2+1. 3. Drag A3 down to row 366.\tOutput: A column of 365 perfect sequential dates. Rationale: Excel logic guarantees no missing days or wrong dates. 1.3\tInject Content\t1. Use ChatGPT to generate 365 short quotes. 2. Paste them into the DailyQuote column. 3. Fill DayOfWeek column using formula =TEXT(A2, \"dddd\").\tOutput: A massive table with unique content for every single page of your planner. Phase 2: The Template (The Skeleton) Tool: Google Slides (Yes, really - it's a layout tool) Step\tAction\tDetailed Walkthrough\tExpected Output 2.1\tPage Setup\t1. Go to File > Page Setup. 2. Select \"Custom\" > 8.5 x 11 inches (or A5 dimensions).\tA print-ready canvas size. 2.2\tDesign the Grid\t1. Use \"Insert Table\" to make your schedule grid. 2. Design one single Master Slide exactly how you want it to look.\tA static template. 2.3\tMap the Tags\t1. Where you want the date, type <<Date>>. 2. Where you want the quote, type <<DailyQuote>>. 3. Use the exact headers from your Google Sheet inside the << >>.\tOutput: A \"Tokenized\" template. Rationale: These tags tell the software where to inject your data. Phase 3: The Merge (The Engine) Tool: Autocrat (Free Google Workspace Add-on) Step\tAction\tClick-by-Click Instructions\tExpected Output 3.1\tInstall Autocrat\t1. In Google Sheets, go to Extensions > Add-ons > Get Add-ons. 2. Search \"Autocrat\" and install.\tThe engine is installed. 3.2\tConfigure Job\t1. Launch Autocrat inside your Sheet. 2. Select Template: Choose the Google Slide you made in Phase 2. 3. Map Tags: It will ask \"What is <>?\" -> Select column Date.\tMapping logic connecting your data to your design. 3.3\tRun the Job\t1. Select Output: \"Single Output Mode\" (Creates one big PDF) or \"Multiple Output Mode\" (365 files). Choose Single. 2. Click Run (Play button).\tOutput: A 365-page PDF appearing in your Google Drive. Rationale: Autocrat takes row 1, fills page 1. Takes row 2, fills page 2. Repeat 365x. Alternative 2: Tangent Templates If the spreadsheet method feels too technical. Tangent Templates is a tool specifically built for Amazon KDP low-content books (planners/journals). It is a one-time purchase (around $59), not a subscription. Pros: It has a massive library of pre-built \"internals\" (fitness logs, crypto trackers, meditation logs). Workflow: You select \"Daily Planner,\" choose your paper size, and it spits out a PDF. Cons: Less customizable design-wise than the Google Method, but faster out of the box. Alternative 3: Book Bolt Studio If you want a SaaS that includes market research. Book Bolt is designed for \"Print on Demand\" sellers. The Feature: It has a \"Drag and Drop\" interior wizard that works like a simplified InDesign. The Edge: It has a \"Maze Generator\" and \"Puzzle Generator\" built-in if you want to make activity books/planners (great for the \"ADHD Planner\" niche). Strategic Recommendation for You Since you are a Product Developer and Digital Marketer: Use the Google Sheets + Autocrat method. Why? It gives you a proprietary asset. You own the source code (the sheet). You can easily outsource this SOP to a VA (\"Here is the sheet, paste new quotes, run the script\"). It costs $0, keeping your margins at 100%. It allows for Dynamic Personalization if you ever sell high-ticket: You could literally ask a client for their name and birthday, put it in the sheet, and generate a planner that says \"Happy Birthday, [Name]\" on their specific date. That is a $100 product, not a $20 product. AI Chat Your AI Employee Free Today Claude Haiku 4.5 Speak"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=fb934e38-5e22-455f-b1d5-a4a7c08f98ec","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=fb934e38-5e22-455f-b1d5-a4a7c08f98ec"}]}]}]
